<a name="ourhistory"></a>
<div class="content bg-240">
    <div class="mid bg-255" style="max-width:100%;">
        <h1 class="greencenter">Our Story</h1>
        <div class="bargray"></div>
        <p class="fortyfivegray">Our story began with Matthew Myles Walsh’s small carpentry business in 1898. Since then, our company has evolved through four generations of family ownership to become the multi-billion dollar contracting business we are today, with more than 8,000 skilled tradespeople and professional staff.<br><br></p>
        <div class="videowrap">
            <div class="videos">
                <div class="mediasquare" onclick="location.href='/media/companyoverview.html';">
                    <div class="contents"><h3>Company Overview</h3></div>
                    <img src="/assets-f/img/89a7071d425f72.jpg" alt="Walsh Corporate">
                    <div class="black"><i class="fa fa-play"></i></div>
                </div>
                <div class="mediasquare" onclick="location.href = '/media/littlegreenfilm.html';">
                    <div class="contents"><h3>Little Green Film</h3></div>
                    <img src="/assets-f/img/52e651e201fccc.jpg" alt="Walsh History">
                    <div class="black"><i class="fa fa-play"></i></div>
                </div>
                <div class="viewall"><a href="#" class="viewall">View Our Media Library</a></div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div style="clear:both;"></div>
    </div>
</div>

<a name="ourtradition"></a>
<div class="content bg-240">
    <div class="mid" style="max-width:100%;">
        <h1 class="greencenter">Our Tradition</h1>
        <div class="bargray"></div>
        <p class="fortyfivegray">We are a company rich in history and tradition. One of our most treasured traditions dates back more than six decades, placing Miraculous Medals in a project’s first concrete pour. The Miraculous Medal is an oval-shaped depiction of Mary according to Saint Catherine Laboure’s vision. The gesture of placing Miraculous Medals symbolizes an inspiration for the workers to successfully complete the job safely. We continue this tradition as a commitment to project, team, company and family.<br><br></p>
        <div class="videowrap">
            <div class="videos">
                <div class="mediasquare" style="width:100%;" onclick="location.href='/ourcompany/ourtradition.html';">
                    <br>
                    <img src="/assets-f/img/2ca53316887a42.jpg" alt="Walsh Corporate">
                </div>
                <div class="viewall"><a href="#" class="viewall">Learn More</a></div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div style="clear:both;"></div>
    </div>
</div>

<a name="executivebios"></a>
<div class="content bg-240">
    <div class="mid bg-255" style="max-width:100%;">
        <h1 class="greencenter">Our Leadership</h1>
        <div class="bargray"></div>
        <div class="executives" style="max-width: 1200px;">
            <div class="executive">
                <div class="execleft"><img src="/assets-f/img/a543b46a5ed7e0.jpg" alt="Daniel J. Walsh - Co-Chairman"></div>
                <div class="execright">
                    <h3><b>DANIEL J. WALSH,</b> CO-CHAIRMAN</h3>
                    <p>As Co-Chairman, Dan takes an active interest in every project constructed by The Walsh Group. His interest has helped to maintain a high level of quality while delivering projects safely and successfully to clients for more than four decades. Dan has been directly responsible for establishing Walsh as a major national contractor, growing company revenues beyond $5 billion, and securing major projects such as LaGuardia Airport Redevelopment, a new International Terminal at Los Angeles International Airport, and Women’s College Hospital. Dan has a deep commitment to family, and incorporates that atmosphere in his business on a day-to-day basis. Dan helped lead the sponsoring of internships for Inner City minority high school students, giving them an opportunity to learn more about the construction industry.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="executive">
                <div class="execleft"><img src="/assets-f/img/bb15c4fbe26119.jpg" alt="Matthew Walsh - Co-Chairman"></div>
                <div class="execright">
                    <h3><b>MATTHEW WALSH,</b> CO-CHAIRMAN</h3>
                    <p>As Co-Chairman, Matt brings more than 50 years of construction experience and real estate development. Matt’s leadership has helped to deliver a high level of quality, safety and customer service for more than four decades. Matt was responsible for leading the firm into the heavy civil industry and growing the company into one of the nation’s largest heavy civil contractors. Matt was directly involved in major US projects such as the reconstruction of the Dan Ryan and Kennedy Expressways in Chicago and the Ohio River Bridge Projects in Indiana and Kentucky, the first P3 Civil project for Walsh and the largest PAB financed project in North America at the time. Matt helped fund the Walsh Foundation which annually provides major grants to the many educational, church and civic charities.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="executive">
                <div class="execleft"><img src="/assets-f/img/1f8e95fb96a426.jpg" alt="Sean Walsh - President - Walsh Construction"></div>
                <div class="execright">
                    <h3><b>SEAN WALSH,</b> PRESIDENT – WALSH CONSTRUCTION</h3>
                    <p>As President of Walsh Construction, Sean represents the fourth generation of family leadership. Sean has more than 30 years of experience and is responsible for overseeing the operations of Walsh Construction. Sean is committed to delivering the highest quality of customer service and safe project delivery. Sean’s passion also includes employee development; he has established two leadership programs directed at forming the future leaders of the company.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="executive">
                <div class="execleft"><img src="/assets-f/img/451fa16adac2db.png" alt="Daniel P. Walsh - President - Archer Western"></div>
                <div class="execright">
                    <h3><b>DANIEL P. WALSH,</b> PRESIDENT – ARCHER WESTERN / PRESIDENT – TRANSPORTATION DIVISION</h3>
                    <p>As President of Archer Western, Dan also represents the fourth generation of family leadership. Dan has over 30 years of experience and is responsible for overseeing the operations of Archer Western, including monitoring start up and staffing, establishment of management systems, supervising project progress, and participating in owner consultations as necessary. Additionally, Dan serves as President of The Walsh Group's Transportation Division, providing executive oversight for all transportation-related management operations. The Walsh Group’s transportation portfolio features a wide range of industry-leading bridge, highway, and transit projects for public and federal clients.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="executive">
                <div class="execleft"><img src="/assets-f/img/bf011db62b63bb.png" alt="Mike Whelan - President - Building Division"></div>
                <div class="execright">
                    <h3><b>MIKE WHELAN,</b> PRESIDENT – BUILDING DIVISION</h3>
                    <p>As President of the Building Division, Mike is responsible for overseeing the national operations of the group’s $2 billion annual revenue. The Building Division focuses on a wide variety of vertical markets including top secret and secret military projects, mission critical work, hotel and conference centers, education facilities, high-rise multi-family, healthcare, light-rails, airport and secure government facilities. His passion is connecting with customers and developing long-term, mutually beneficial working relationships.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="executive">
                <div class="execleft"><img src="/assets-f/img/4c7db65a6b7c74.jpg" alt="Duane Petersen - President - Water Division"></div>                
                <div class="execright">
                    <h3><b>DUANE PETERSEN,</b> PRESIDENT – WATER DIVISION</h3>
                    <p>As President of our national Water Division, Duane is responsible for overseeing all of our water operations. Duane brings an incredible understanding of the water industry that has helped the company become an industry leader in water and wastewater treatment facilities. He also specializes in collaborative delivery projects, including construction manager at-risk, design-build and progressive design-build. </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div style="clear:both;"></div>
    </div>
</div>

<script>

    ; (function ($) {
        $.fn.rwdImageMaps = function () {
            var $img = this;

            var rwdImageMap = function () {
                $img.each(function () {
                    if (typeof ($(this).attr('usemap')) == 'undefined')
                        return;

                    var that = this,
                        $that = $(that);

                    // Since WebKit doesn't know the height until after the image has loaded, perform everything in an onload copy
                    $('<img />').load(function () {
                        var attrW = 'width',
                            attrH = 'height',
                            w = $that.attr(attrW),
                            h = $that.attr(attrH);

                        if (!w || !h) {
                            var temp = new Image();
                            temp.src = $that.attr('src');
                            if (!w)
                                w = temp.width;
                            if (!h)
                                h = temp.height;
                        }

                        var wPercent = $that.width() / 100,
                            hPercent = $that.height() / 100,
                            map = $that.attr('usemap').replace('#', ''),
                            c = 'coords';

                        $('map[name="' + map + '"]').find('area').each(function () {
                            var $this = $(this);
                            if (!$this.data(c))
                                $this.data(c, $this.attr(c));

                            var coords = $this.data(c).split(','),
                                coordsPercent = new Array(coords.length);

                            for (var i = 0; i < coordsPercent.length; ++i) {
                                if (i % 2 === 0)
                                    coordsPercent[i] = parseInt(((coords[i] / w) * 100) * wPercent);
                                else
                                    coordsPercent[i] = parseInt(((coords[i] / h) * 100) * hPercent);
                            }
                            $this.attr(c, coordsPercent.toString());
                        });
                    }).attr('src', $that.attr('src'));
                });
            };
            $(window).resize(rwdImageMap).trigger('resize');

            return this;
        };
    })(jQuery);


    function setCircles() {

        for (var i = 0; i < $("div.process div.circle").size() ; i++) {

            var numTop = parseInt(($('div.circle').outerHeight() - $('div.process div.circle div.num').eq(i).outerHeight()) / 2);
            $('div.process div.circle div.num').eq(i).css('margin-top', numTop + 'px');
            $('div.process div.circle:hover div.num').eq(i).css('margin-top', numTop + 'px');

            var copyTop = parseInt(($('div.circle').outerHeight() - $('div.process div.circle div.copy').eq(i).outerHeight()) / 2);
            $('div.process div.circle div.copy').eq(i).css('margin-top', copyTop + 'px');
            $('div.process div.circle:hover div.copy').eq(i).css('margin-top', copyTop + 'px');
        }

    }

    function setExecutiveHeight() {
        var max = -1;
        $('div.executive').css("height", "auto");
        $("div.executive").each(function () {
            var h = $(this).height();
            max = h > max ? h : max;
        });
        $('div.executive').css("height", max + "px");
    }

    $(document).ready(function (e) {

        $('img[usemap]').rwdImageMaps();
        setCircles();

        var enterEvent = "touchstart";
        var leaveEvent = "touchend";

        //var touch_capable = 'ontouchstart' in window || window.DocumentTouch && document instanceof window.DocumentTouch || navigator.maxTouchPoints > 0 || window.navigator.msMaxTouchPoints > 0;

        //if (touch_capable) {
        //if (!("ontouchstart" in window)) {
        // if no touch we use mouseenter and mouseleave events
        enterEvent = "mouseenter";
        leaveEvent = "mouseleave";
        //}

        if ($(document).width() > 767) {
            //$(".locations area").on(enterEvent, function (e) {
            $(".locations area").mouseover(function () {
                var idx = $(".locations area").index(this);
                var position = $(".locations area:eq(" + idx + ")").attr('coords').split(',');
                x = +position[0] + 25;
                y = +position[1] - 75;
                //$(".map-hovers div:eq(" + idx + ")").css("display", "block");
                $(".map-hovers div:eq(" + idx + ")").css("left", x + 'px');
                $(".map-hovers div:eq(" + idx + ")").css("top", y + 'px');
                //$(".map-hovers div:eq(" + idx + ")").animate({ opacity: 1 }, 500, function () { });
                $(".map-hovers div:eq(" + idx + ")").stop(true, true).fadeIn(800);
                // $(".map-hovers div:eq(" + idx + ")").show();
                return false;
            });

            //$(".locations area").on(leaveEvent, function (e) {
            $(".locations area").mouseout(function () {
                //$(".map-hovers div").hide();
                var idx = $(".locations area").index(this);
                //$(".map-hovers div:eq(" + idx + ")").animate({ opacity: 0 }, 500, function () { });
                $(".map-hovers div:eq(" + idx + ")").stop(true, true).fadeOut(800);
                return false;
            });
        }
        //setExecutiveHeight();
    });

    $(window).resize(function () {
        setCircles();
        //  setExecutiveHeight();
    });

    $('body').bind('beforeunload', function () {
        setCircles();
        // setExecutiveHeight();
    });

</script>



